label.value: positive regulation of transforming growth factor beta2 production

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of production of transforming growth factor-beta2.

label.value: positive regulation of transforming growth factor beta3 production

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of production of transforming growth factor-beta3.
The modification of polyamines by addition of acetyl groups.
The modification of spermidine by addition of acetyl groups.
The modification of spermine by addition of acetyl groups.
The modification of putrescine by addition of acetyl groups.
A complex consisting of 4 protein subunits as a heterotetramer, that possesses sarcosine oxidase activity.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression such that an expression pattern recurs with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of phosphonates, any organic compound containing one or more C-PO(OH)2 or C-PO(OR)2 (with R=alkyl, aryl) groups. Synthesis of phosphonic acid itself, an inorganic compound without the biochemically relevant C-P bond, is not included.

The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to an activin receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: regulation of activin receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of any activin receptor signaling pathway.

label.value: negative regulation of activin receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of any activin receptor signaling pathway.

label.value: positive regulation of activin receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of any activin receptor signaling pathway.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of enzymatic generation of superoxide by a cell.

label.value: negative regulation of superoxide anion generation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of enzymatic generation of superoxide by a cell.

label.value: positive regulation of superoxide anion generation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of enzymatic generation of superoxide by a cell.
Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + histone H3 L-lysine (position 56) = CoA + histone H3 N6-acetyl-L-lysine (position 56).

label.value: negative regulation of astral microtubule depolymerization

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the depolymerization of astral microtubules.

The series of molecular signals from the endoplasmic reticulum to the nucleus generated as a consequence of decreased levels of one or more sterols (and in some yeast, changes in oxygen levels) and which proceeds through activation of a sterol response element binding transcription factor (SREBP) to result in up-regulation of target gene transcription.
Binding to a sterol, a steroid containing a hydroxy group in the 3 position, closely related to cholestan-3-ol.
Binding to and responding, e.g. by conformational change, to changes in the cellular level of a sterol.

A protein complex formed by the association of sterol regulatory element binding protein (SREBP) and SREBP-cleavage-activating protein (SCAP) in the ER membrane; in the absence of sterols, the SREBP-SCAP complex is packaged into COPII vesicles and travels to the Golgi apparatus to be processed.

A protein complex formed by the association of sterol regulatory element binding protein (SREBP), SREBP-cleavage-activating protein (SCAP), and an Insig protein (Insig-1 or Insig-2) in the ER membrane.

label.value: negative regulation of translation in response to oxidative stress

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of translation as a result of oxidative stress, a state often resulting from exposure to high levels of reactive oxygen species, e.g. superoxide anions, hydrogen peroxide (H2O2), and hydroxyl radicals.

label.value: positive regulation of translation in response to oxidative stress

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of translation as a result of oxidative stress, a state often resulting from exposure to high levels of reactive oxygen species, e.g. superoxide anions, hydrogen peroxide (H2O2), and hydroxyl radicals.
The controlled release of a substance by a cell.
The controlled release of a substance by a tissue.
Catalysis of the reaction: 1D-myo-inositol 1,4,5,6-tetrakisphosphate + ATP = 1D-myo-inositol 1,2,4,5,6-pentakisphosphate + ADP + H+.
The expansion of a mononuclear cell population by cell division. A mononuclear cell is a leukocyte with a single non-segmented nucleus in the mature form.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mononuclear cell proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of mononuclear cell proliferation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mononuclear cell proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of mononuclear cell proliferation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mononuclear cell proliferation.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving alpha-glucans.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways relusting in the formation of alpha-glucans.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving beta-glucans.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways relusting in the formation of beta-glucans.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving (1->3)-beta-D-glucans.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of (1->3)-beta-D-glucans.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a cytokinetic process.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of division septum formation. Division septum formation is the assembly and arrangement of a septum that spans the plasma membrane interface between progeny cells following cytokinesis.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins.
The chemical reactions and pathways involving myo-inositol phosphate, 1,2,3,4,5,6-cyclohexanehexol, with three phosphate groups attached.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of an inositol phosphate, 1,2,3,4,5,6-cyclohexanehexol, with one or more phosphate groups attached.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of inositol trisphosphate, 1,2,3,4,5,6-cyclohexanehexol, with three phosphate groups attached.

label.value: regulation of inositol trisphosphate biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of inositol trisphosphate.

label.value: negative regulation of inositol trisphosphate biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of inositol trisphosphate.

label.value: positive regulation of inositol trisphosphate biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of inositol trisphosphate.

The chemical reactions and pathways involving collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals. Collagen is highly enriched in glycine (some regions are 33% glycine) and proline, occurring predominantly as 3-hydroxyproline (about 20%).

The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals. Collagen is highly enriched in glycine (some regions are 33% glycine) and proline, occurring predominantly as 3-hydroxyproline (about 20%).

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals.
